<p>The superstar and his entourage were rumoured to have spent 14 days isolating in a lavish Gold Coast mansion after being granted an exemption from hotel quarantine. </p>

<p>While thousands of Australians are forced to stay in shoe box-sized hotel rooms guarded by the military, the A-lister and his cohorts were reported to be relaxing on the 55-acre grounds at the Rivermead Estate in Queensland.</p>

<p>But both the estate owners and the Queensland government have denied the rumours, with Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk insisting Hanks was staying in a Queensland Health-approved hotel.</p>

